This project PORTS (adapts) specific pieces from the projects below — it does NOT
vendor verbatim copies. Ported code carries a per-file provenance header naming its
origin, and each port is verified against ground truth (mx.vjp / a reference oracle).

1. anthropics/jacobian-lens (Apache License 2.0) — THE PRIMARY FITTING REFERENCE.
   The reference Jacobian-lens implementation and the paper "Verbalizable
   Representations Form a Global Workspace in Language Models". Its torch-autograd fit
   loop (fitting.py) is translated to mx.vjp; its design is adopted directly — the
   norm kept OUTSIDE J and applied as the real module at decode, and the chain-free
   end-to-end per-layer Jacobian. Used via the fork github.com/fblissjr/jacobian-lens.

2. WeZZard/jlens-qwen36 (Apache License 2.0) — one optional piece only.
   MLX on-device fitting for the qwen3_5 (Gated-DeltaNet hybrid) architecture. Its
   role here is a single optional accelerator — the custom Metal GDN backward kernel +
   analytic branch-Jacobian assembly — which we PORT into jlens_mlx/ only when the
   direct-VJP baseline is too slow on the 27B, verified vs mx.vjp and attributed.
   NOT vendored. (Note: its closed-form RMSNorm-Jacobian has an rms**2/rms**3 bug we
   caught and avoid — see the plan's observations.)

3. solarkyle/jspace (Apache License 2.0) — research/asset reference, not a dependency.
   A same-day replication built on the Anthropic reference; the origin of pre-fit
   lenses (solarkyle/jspace-lenses) and the hallucination-router design. Source of
   downstream analysis ideas (hallucination anatomy, lie detection, uncertainty probes).

4. Neuronpedia (MIT) — design inspiration only, no code. The production interp
   platform; the model-agnostic apply/decode contract (real final norm + config
   softcap + matmul-only transport) and the layer-navigation / intervention UX
   informed this project's direction.

Reference clones live outside this repo (a sibling coderef/ directory), not committed here.
